__NOTOC__ {{Infobox OS |name = nUbuntu |logo = [[Image:NUBLogo.png|center|nUbuntu|250px]] |screenshot = [[Image:Nubuntu-8.12-beta.png|250px]] <!-- Unsourced image removed: [[image:NUbuntuscreen.jpg|250px]] --> |caption = nUbuntu - Formula One |developer = Brendan Almonte, Emanuele Gentili, Jayson Beitler |family = [[Unix-like]] / [[Linux]] / [[Debian]] / [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] |source_model = [[Free software]]/ [[Open Source Software]] |latest_release_version = 8.12 |latest_release_date = {{release date|2008|12|16}} |kernel_type = [[Linux]] |ui = [[Fluxbox]] |license = Mainly [[GNU GPL]] / Various |working_state = Discontinued |website = [http://www.nubuntu.org/ www.nubuntu.org] }} {{lowercase|title=nUbuntu}} '''nUbuntu''' or '''Network Ubuntu''' was a project to take the existing [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] [[operating system]] LiveCD and Full Installer and remaster it with tools needed for [[penetration testing]] servers and [[Computer network|networks]]. The main idea is to keep Ubuntu's ease of use and mix it with popular penetration testing tools. Besides usage for network and server testing, nUbuntu will be made to be a desktop distribution for advanced Linux users.{{Citation needed|date=March 2009}}
== Contents == nUbuntu uses the light [[window manager]] [[Fluxbox]].
It includes some of the most used security programs for Linux, such as [[Wireshark]], [[nmap]], [[dSniff]], and [[Ettercap (computing)|Ettercap]].
== History == * 2005-12-18 - nUbuntu Project is born, developers release Testing 1 * 2006-01-16 - nUbuntu Live developers release Stable 1 * 2006-06-26 - nUbuntu Live developers release version 6.06 * 2006-10-16 - nUbuntu featured in [http://www.byakuya-shobo.co.jp/hj/ Hacker Japan], a Japanese hacker magazine http://www.byakuya-shobo.co.jp/hj/info3.html#2006_11 * 2006-11-21 - nUbuntu Live developers release version 6.10 * 2007-12-31 - nUbuntu developer Tom Bell retires from project, Brendan Almonte takes over{{Citation needed|date=March 2009}} * 2008-11-12 - [http://www.gerix.it Gerix IT Security Solutions] become a nUbuntu Technical Partner{{Citation needed|date=March 2009}}
As of April 4, 2010, the official website is closed with no explanation.
